cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.DB, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with load balancing in distributed stream processing systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel load balancing technique that uses a heaving hitter algorithm to efficiently identify the hottest keys in the stream. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of distributed stream processing systems. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper deals with processing data streams. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a technique to improve the throughput and latency of distributed stream processing systems.
